name: TreeViewItem
description:
An individual tree node.
Renders a `<div>` element.

value.description:
A unique value that identifies this tree item.
This is required and used for expansion and selection.

index.description:
The index of the item in the list.
Used for virtualization to improve performance.

disabled.description: Whether this item should ignore user interaction.

className.description:
CSS class applied to the element, or a function that
returns a class based on the component’s state.

style.detailedType:
| React.CSSProperties
| ((
    state: TreeView.Item.State,
  ) => CSSProperties | undefined)
| undefined

render.description:
Allows you to replace the component’s HTML element
with a different tag, or compose it with another component.

Accepts a `ReactElement` or a function that returns the element to render.
render.detailedType:
| ReactElement
| ((
    props: HTMLProps,
    state: TreeView.Item.State,
  ) => ReactElement)
